  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOPT / PARC West Bank: Covid-19 Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project addresses COVID-19 in the Jordan Valley OPT, responding to the immediate need to minimise the spread of the virus as well as the impact of lockdown and economic consequences thereof.  It also creates a sustainable long-term solution for community resilience and food security, both of which are areas of the humanitarian country plan that are currently not well funded. Crucially, this deals with the long-term issues facing communities in OPT, the most prevalent at the moment being threatened annexation.


Marj - Na&apos;jaa and Al-Zbiedat, two neighbouring Palestinian villages located east of the West Bank (Area C), will be targeted by:
1) Supporting food security and hygiene, through the rehabilitation of a ground water well 

2) Supporting the prevention of Covid-19 among farmers
3) Improving resilience and preparedness of communities at risk, by establishing a Community Protection Committee in each of the communities (5 men and 5 women) using the PVCA approach developed with Christian Aid.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food production is increased and food security improved in the two villages for 3,200 people. These people will also have increased resilience and capacity to deal with the long-term shocks, political and health related.</narrative>
  </description>
